articles.title: About me:
articles.description:
I am an evolutionary biologist and social psychologist (Ph. D. from University of New South Wales, Sydney Australia).

Currently I work as a data analyst for the [Atlas of Living Australia](https://www.ala.org.au/).

I am interested in understanding evolutionary and cultural underpinnings of human behaviour; in particular, sexist attitudes and behaviours. I published a few papers on this at one point.

I value scientific transparency and reproducibility. I try to implement these practices as much as I can.

Passionate about music. Love all genres. I play piano sometimes.

I make several Spotify playlists. You might like to listen to them sometime:
